  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "Instagram doesn't provide a feature that shows you the specific usernames of everyone who has viewed your videos, except for a few cases:\n\n*   **Stories:** If your video is posted as an Instagram Story, you can see the list of users who viewed it for 24 hours after you post it. This is done by swiping up on your own story.\n\n*   **Reels:** You can see the number of views for your reels, but not the specific usernames of the viewers.\n\n*   **Instagram Live:** When you go live, you'll see the number of viewers watching. After the live video ends, you can see the number of people who watched it live, but not their usernames.\n\n*   **Videos Posted to your Feed:** You'll see the view count, but not a list of viewers.",
